item.title: [ENTESB-6004] CXF Synchronous response listener is not working with WMQ during reconnect
item.description:
• If we refresh the bundle( having camel-route), issue is resolved.
  • I further tried increasing start-level of this bundle, but issue persists. We need to refresh the bundle to resolve issue.
item.summary: CXF Synchronous response listener is not working with WMQ during reconnect

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
• Unzip the project MQ_POC_replyTo.zip.
  • Modify blueprint.xml to refer file consumer to local system path. 

    <from uri="file:/path/to/folder_to_polll/" />

  • Build project using command `mvn clean install`
  • Deploy it in Fuse environment using command 

    features:install cxf-transports-jms
    		 
    osgi:install -s mvn:com.mycompany/WMQ_POC_replyTo/1.0.0-SNAPSHOT

  • Paste file TestSoap.txt to folder set above. This file is provided within project.
  • It should run fine.
  • Now go to the testlab for IBM MQ server. 

    ssh mqm@lab-webspheremq-1.gsslab.rdu2.redhat.com
    		 
    #stop MQ server
    		 
    $ /opt/mqm/bin/endmqm QMA
    		 
    $ /opt/mqm/bin/endmqlsr -m QMA

  • Now again drop TestSoap.txt file to folder.
  • We observe timeout error.
